				<note resp="Philip Lampi">"Extract of a letter from a Gentleman in New Haven, to his Friend in this town, dated October 31. - We have this moment concluded the choice of Electors they are .... These Gentleman were all chosen by an almost unanimous Vote in the House of Representative, and without a dissenting Voice in the Council. They are firm Federalist, and will act upon New England Principles and Politics."  The United States Chronicle (Providence, RI).  November 6, 1800.</note>
